    • mod_appt

      public void mod_appt(javafx.event.ActionEvent actionEvent)
      LAMBDA FUNCTION PRESENT*** This lambda passes the required parameters to the functional "check" interface method. This creates a "popup" alert of the type passed in with the title and message. This allows for the creation of a popup within the controller logic and shortens the within controller logic down considerably.
      As a note I would not have typically put this inside of one particular interface method but defined outside and then used in multiple different instances however to meet requirements the lambda needed to be inside a particular method so that I could comment and point it out. If used multiple times however this would have made the creating of the "Check" worth it in terms of code brevity as each subsequent alert could have been just the one line "check.popUp(**insert arguments**"" etc.

      Additionally this mod appointment function brings the mod appointment pane to front and pre-fills the fields with data from the selected appointment from the appointments table.

    • delete_appt

      public void delete_appt(javafx.event.ActionEvent actionEvent)
      Deletes from the database the appointment that corresponds to the selected appointment from the table. Confirms this action and if there is no selection gives an error message indicating as such. Provides a popup of deleted appointment information on success.

    • onSaveAdd

      public void onSaveAdd(javafx.event.ActionEvent actionEvent) throws SQLException
      Calls the validation function (this is passed to an alert as long as there is something to alert about remaining) and once this passes inputs information from fields into a new appointment object and passes the object to the appointmentsDAO.addAppointment() function to be added to database. Finally, resets the appointment table, clears the form fields and moves the home pane to front.
      Throws:
      SQLException

    • onCancelMod

      public void onCancelMod(javafx.event.ActionEvent actionEvent)
      Moves home pane to front if modification is canceled.

    • onSaveMod

      public void onSaveMod(javafx.event.ActionEvent actionEvent) throws SQLException
      Calls the validation function (this is passed to an alert as long as there is something to alert about remaining) and once this passes, inputs information from fields into a new appointment object and passes the object to the appointmentsDAO.updateAppointment() function to be added to database. Finally, resets the appointment table and moves the home pane to front.
      Throws:
      SQLException

    • onMonth

      public void onMonth(javafx.event.ActionEvent actionEvent)

    • setApptTable

      private void setApptTable()
      Function refreshes the appointments table. Will refresh the data in the table with all appointments, this month's appointments, or this week's appointments depending on the current state of the toggle group of radio buttons.

    • validateAdd

      private String validateAdd() throws SQLException
      Insures that all data inputted into the add appointment form fields pass specified requirements. For each separate requirement that does not pass a specific error is provided and the complete error message is returned.
      Returns:
      a string which is the complete error message with a specific indication for each error found.

      SQLException
